long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1268013 journalctl output
Description of problem: Boot kernel 4.10.5-200.fc25.x86_64 or 4.10.6-200.fc25.x86_64 and kernel encounters general protection fault
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): kernel 4.10.5-200.fc25.x86_64 or 4.10.6-200.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: No special action required.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Boot one of the kernels described above. 2. Login to Gnome desktop 3.
Actual results: System hangs.
Expected results:
Additional info: Protection fault occurs at Mar 31 18:44:80 in log file.

Any update? This continues to be a problem with all new kernels.
Running:
Linux eddy 4.9.14-200.fc25.x86_64 #1 SMP Mon Mar 13 19:26:40 UTC 2017 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux
Without a problem so is there a work around?
Entirely possible that your fix will be in 4.10.12. It should release tomorrow.
The fix in question has been queued for 4.10-stable too: commit 2907e8670b6ef253bffb33bf47fd2182969cf2a0 in the stable tree.
